So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:--------------------------------------------------------------------The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in Gokuldham Co-operative Society and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Shailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi / Raj Anadkat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:-------------------------------------------The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in Gokuldham Co-operative Society and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble for all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. description: Vrat ke kadhi chawal, Vrat ka Khana, singhare ki kadhi, navratri chawal, farali kadhi, vrat kadhi recipe, navratri pulao, vrat ki recipe, vrat ke chawal banane ki vidhi, vrat khana recipe,#NavratriSpecial #VratKaKhana #KadhiChawalForVrat ngredients for Falari Kadhi ChawalFor Pakoda:Water Chestnut Flour - ‡§∏‡§ø‡§Ç‡§ò‡§æ‡•ú‡•á ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§Ü‡§ü‡§æ - 2 tbspCurd - ‡§¶‡§π‡•Ä - 2 tbspGinger - ‡§Ö‡§¶‡§∞‡§ï - 1/2 tsp, gratedRock Salt - ‡§∏‡•à‡§Ç‡§ß‡§æ ‡§®‡§Æ‡§ï - 1/4 tspGreen Chilli - ‡§π‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö - 1, finely choppedCoriander Leaves - ‡§π‡§∞‡§æ ‡§ß‡§®‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ - 1 tspPotato - ‡§Ü‡§≤‡•Ç -1Black Pepper - ‡§ï‡§æ‡§≤‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö - 1/4 tsp, coarsely ground and oil for fryingfor KadhiCurd - ‡§¶‡§π‡•Ä - 1/2 CupWater Chestnut Flour - ‡§∏‡§ø‡§Ç‡§ò‡§æ‡•ú‡•á ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§Ü‡§ü‡§æ - 2 tbspOil - ‡§§‡•á‡§≤ - 1 tbspCumin Seeds - ‡§ú‡•Ä‡§∞‡§æ - 1/2 tspGreen Chilli - ‡§π‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö - 2Green Chilli - ‡§π‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö - 2, finely choppedGinger - ‡§Ö‡§¶‡§∞‡§ï - 1/2 tsp, gratedCurry Leaves - ‡§ï‡•ú‡•Ä ‡§™‡§§‡•ç‡§§‡§æ - 5-6Black Pepper - ‡§ï‡§æ‡§≤‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö - 1/4 tsp, coarsely groundRock Salt - ‡§∏‡•à‡§Ç‡§ß‡§æ ‡§®‡§Æ‡§ï - 1/2 tspCoriander Leaves - ‡§π‡§∞‡§æ ‡§ß‡§®‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ - 2-3 tsspFor Rice:Desi Ghee - ‡§ò‡•Ä - 1 tspCumin Seeds - ‡§ú‡•Ä‡§∞‡§æ - 1/2 tspBarnyard Millet - ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§æ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§ö‡§æ‡§µ‡§≤ - 1/2 Cup (100 grams)Rock Salt - ‡§∏‡•à‡§Ç‡§ß‡§æ ‡§®‡§Æ‡§ï - 1/4 tspKadhi Chawal for Navratri Fasting1. First, start with preparing pakora for the Kadhi. Take 2 tbsp of singhara flour and add 2 tbsp of curd to it. 2. Add 1-chopped green chili, 1/2 tsp grated ginger, 1/4 tsp rock salt, 1 tsp green coriander, 1chopped potato, 1/4 tsp black pepper to the batter and mix well. 3. Add 1 tbsp of water to the batter and mix well.  Heat the oil for frying the Pakoda. We need medium-high hot oil for frying.4. Put the pakoda in the oil for frying. Fry the pakoras over medium flame till golden brown. Similarly, prepare all the pakora. 5. Now, prepare the mixture for Kadhi. Take 1/2 cup of curd, add 2 tbsp of singhara flour, and mix well. 6. Add 1.5 cups of water to the mixture, and the curry mixture is ready. Take a kadhai to prepare Kadhi. 7. Heat 1 tbsp of oil in the Kadhai. Add 1/2 tsp of jeera, 2chilies with cut mark lengthways, 2chopped chilies, 1/2 tsp of grated ginger, and 5-6 curry leaves to the oil.8. Pour the curry mixture in the Kadhai and stir simultaneously. Cook while stirring till it starts boiling.9. After a boil, stop stirring, lower the flame, add 1/2 tsp rock salt, 1/4 tsp of crushed black pepper, and simmer the curry for 10-12 mins.10. After 7-8 mins, add pakora to the curry and simmer the curry with pakora for 5-6 mins. 11. After 12 mins, add green coriander and transfer the curry to the serving plate. 12. To prepare rice, take a cooker and add 1 tsp of ghee to it. When the ghee is hot, add 1/2 tsp of jeera and roast them lightly. 13. Next, add 1/2 cup of Samak rice and roast them lightly in the ghee. Add 1 cup water, 1/4 tsp of rock salt to the rice, and mix well.14. Close the cooker and pressure cook the rice for 1-whistle. After a whistle, turn off the flame and wait for the cooker's pressure to settle. 15. After that, transfer the rice to the serving plate and enjoy it with curry and pakora. description: Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 Click here to watch all your favorite Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gqFEadNxmd8&list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:--------------------------------------------------------------------The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in Gokuldham Co-operative Society and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Shailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi / Raj Anadkat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. description: Do you feel like you fell out of love with your spouse or intimate partner? Are you feeling really annoyed by her or his mannerisms or idiosyncrasies? Does it seem like your relationship is in a rut and perhaps you feel bored? When you think about your intimate partner, do negative thoughts and feelings get in the way of seeing what you used to value and still could appreciate?If your answer to the above questions is a big 'YES', then you aren't far from what this couple is going through.Meet Aman and Veena, a young couple who have reached a breaking point in their relationship. They're on the verge of a break-up when Veena discovers an online article which might just help them save their relationship. This couple is desperate to do anything to revive the spark, even if it means listening to something as silly as a cosmopolitan article titled 5 ways to reignite your relationship.  Will this be enough? Or is this the last chapter of their love story? Watch our Flick '5+1 ways to fall in love (again)' to find out.#Love #Flick #TheZoomStudiosDo you ever get a feeling that your life could be made into a movie? The lows and highs, games you lost, friends you won, the first kiss, the first day of college, the first paycheck. Our life is in fact nothing short of a film. A film made of these moments that we have lived or would want to live someday.
